<!DOCTYPE frameset SYSTEM "frameset.dtd">
<frameset>
    <predicate lemma="throw">
        <note>
            Frames file for 'throw' based on sentences in financial subcorpus.
            Verbnet entry throw-17.1, other framed members include fire kick and
            pass.  Comparison to 'cast'.
        </note>
        
        <roleset id="throw.01" name="throw" vncls="17.1">
            <roles>
                <role descr="thrower" n="0">
                    
                    <vnrole vncls="17.1" vntheta="Agent"/>
                </role>
                
                <role descr="thing thrown" n="1">
                    
                    <vnrole vncls="17.1" vntheta="Patient"/>
                </role>
                
                <role descr="thrown at, to, over, etc" n="2">
                    
                    <vnrole vncls="17.1" vntheta="Destination"/>
                </role>
                
            </roles>
            
            <example name="idiom: throw in the towel">
                <text>
                    [Thermo Electron]-1 acquired some 6% of Milton Roy's common stock
                    before *trace*-1 throwing in the towel and reducing its stake in
                    early September. 
                </text>
                <arg n="0">*trace*</arg>
                <rel>throwing</rel>
                <arg n="2">in</arg>
                <arg n="1">the towel</arg>
                <arg f="TMP" n="M">in early September</arg>
            </example>
            
            <example name="throw into doubt">
                <text>
                    In the wake of Campeau's problems, prices of junk bonds tumbled,
                    *trace* throwing into doubt the ability of corporate acquirers to
                    finance large takeovers with the help of junk bond sales. 
                </text>
                <arg n="0">*trace*</arg>
                <rel>throwing</rel>
                <arg n="2">into doubt</arg>
                <arg n="1">the ability of corporate acquirers to finance large
                    takeovers with the help of junk bond sales
                </arg>
            </example>
            
            <note>
                The trace points to the event of &quot;prices of junk bonds tumbled&quot;, which
                is not a constituent in the tree.  Therefore the trace gets no target.
            </note>
            
            <example name="another direction">
                <text>
                    ``[Stocks]-1 were being thrown *trace*-1 out of windows at any price.'' 
                </text>
                <rel>thrown</rel>
                <arg n="1">*trace*</arg>
                <arg n="2">out of windows</arg>
                <arg n="M">at any price</arg>
            </example>
            
            <note>
            </note>
            
        </roleset>
        
        <roleset id="throw.03" name="hold" vncls="-">
            <roles>
                <role descr="holder" n="0"/>
                <role descr="thing held" n="1"/>
            </roles>
            
            <example name="throw a party">
                <text>
                    In an invention that drives Verdi purists bananas, Violetta lies
                    dying in bed during the prelude, rising deliriously when then she
                    remembers the great parties *trace-1* [she]-2 used *trace-2* to throw
                    *trace-3*. 
                </text>
                <arg n="0">*trace-2*</arg>
                <rel>throw</rel>
                <arg n="1">*trace-3*</arg>
                <arg n="M" f="RCL">*trace-1* -&gt;  the great parties</arg>
            </example>
            
            <note>
            </note>
            
        </roleset>
